remarks.para:
 To use this class, the application's backup agent class should extend
 .  Then, in the agent's
  method, an instance of this class should be
 allocated and installed as a backup/restore handler within the BackupAgentHelper
 framework.  For example, an agent supporting backup and restore for
 an application with two groups of 
 data might look something like this:
 namespace Backup
{
	public class MyBackupAgent : BackupAgentHelper
	{
		// The name of the SharedPreferences groups that the application maintains. These
		// are the same strings that are passed to the GetSharedPreferences(String, int).
		static String PREFS_DISPLAY = "displayprefs";
		static String PREFS_SCORES = "highscores";

		// An arbitrary string used within the BackupAgentHelper implementation
		// to identify the SharedPreferenceBackupHelper's data.
		static String MY_PREFS_BACKUP_KEY = "myprefs";

		// Simply allocate a helper and install it
		void onCreate() {
			SharedPreferencesBackupHelper helper =
				new SharedPreferencesBackupHelper(this, PREFS_DISPLAY, PREFS_SCORES);
			AddHelper(MY_PREFS_BACKUP_KEY, helper);
		}
	}
}
